title: An evening with Jenny Bryan
description: Jenny Bryan is coming to the area and she would like to have a meetup with our group. If you aren’t familiar with her work, Jenny became internet famous for the website that accompanied her STAT 545 course at University of British Columbia. Since then she has transitioned to working on Hadley Wickham’s tidyverse team at RStudio. She is a wonderful friend, a great mom, and a successful woman in academia and tech.

title: Happy Hour/Tidy Tuesday Data Play/Tips and Tricks
description: If you are able to make it, lets get together Thursday at Pinos for a happy hour/play with Tidy Tuesday data/learn new tricks. Come on by after work, I’ll be there all evening although music starts at 7:30 so it will get a little louder up front, but we can hide out in the back. Bring your laptop!

title: July Meetup - TidyTuesday on a Monday
description:
We will be exploring the TidyTuesday data set of the week when it launches on a Monday. This is a fun, casual way to learn about cleaning data and creating new visualizations and to have side conversations about your favorite R topic and connect with other R-Ladies who might know how to solve that hurdle you’ve been struggling with.

I’m working on wrangling beer, wine, and pizza for the event. If you have food restrictions please let me know.

Also message me to join our slack for easier communication.

Can’t wait to see you all :)

title: First meeting - meet and greet
description: Come out and meet your fellow R-Ladies at the local pub. This is a casual first meeting to get to know each other and figure out what sort of future meeting will best fit people's expectations. Please RSVP so we make sure we have enough room for everyone. See you soon!
